# ─── Pioneer Agent Environment ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# In production, Pioneer Desktop injects needed values from the vault at
# runtime — there is no .env file in the container. This .example exists
# only for LOCAL development bootstrap.
#
# The real `.env` is gitignored and MUST NEVER be committed.
#
# Credentials for tool calls are NOT set here. Tools declare the vault key
# they need in tools.d/*.toml; at call time the agent asks the Pioneer
# Desktop gateway to resolve the value.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Pioneer gateway URL — the agent's only trusted credential source.
# Default: http://127.0.0.1:11411 (Pioneer Desktop local gateway).
# PIONEER_GATEWAY_URL=http://127.0.0.1:11411

# Local-dev fallback API key (optional). Only used when pioneer_auth is
# disabled in config.toml. Leave unset in any real deployment.
# ZEROCLAW_API_KEY=

# Channel bot tokens — if you're running a bot channel locally without the
# vault, you can stub tokens here. Production: these come from the vault.
# DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=
# TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=
# SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=
